WEBVTT

00:00.917 --> 00:02.250
What kind of man are you
Mr. Mason?

00:03.125 --> 00:05.458
PERRY MASON: A piss-poor one,
if I were to be honest.

00:06.500 --> 00:08.291
Let's just say I'm trying
to make up for it.

00:08.458 --> 00:10.417
♪ ("PERRY MASON" THEME MUSIC
PLAYS) ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:11.792
Emily!

00:12.000 --> 00:13.458
The Radiant Assembly might not
have your

00:13.792 --> 00:14.875
best interest at heart.

00:15.250 --> 00:17.792
-No one there has ever hurt me.
-Thank you.

00:18.625 --> 00:20.458
How much debt, would
these records say

00:20.792 --> 00:21.834
that the Church was carrying?

00:21.917 --> 00:24.375
-Just over 100,000 dollars.
-(CROWD GASPS)

00:24.458 --> 00:27.375
Mr. Baggerly, did you give
the Radiant Assembly the money?

00:27.458 --> 00:28.458
I did not.

00:29.333 --> 00:32.500
MASON:
Charlie Dodson is kidnapped
for an attempted extortion...

00:32.583 --> 00:33.375
(SCREAMS)

00:33.458 --> 00:35.500
...of one hundred thousand
dollars.

00:36.959 --> 00:39.500
I can't get on the stand.
Mason will tear me apart.

00:39.792 --> 00:42.125
He can't call you,
if he can't find you.

00:44.417 --> 00:45.625
PAUL DRAKE:
Novak and Cerakney.

00:46.125 --> 00:47.709
They had a kid with them,
wouldn't stop crying.

00:47.959 --> 00:49.625
A third man shows up
with his wife,

00:49.834 --> 00:51.000
then no more crying.

00:51.417 --> 00:54.166
Ennis. What's happens to
an infant nursing

00:54.375 --> 00:55.625
from a junked-up mother?

00:55.709 --> 00:56.750
ENNIS: They'd suffocate.

00:57.000 --> 00:58.166
Don't do this.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.333
My baby.

01:05.250 --> 01:06.208
Charlie Dodson lives.

01:06.792 --> 01:09.709
You did this.
Alice! Alice!

01:10.041 --> 01:11.125
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:17.166 --> 01:20.291
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:34.208 --> 01:37.959
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:38.041 --> 01:39.792
MALE ACOLYTE: We have
ten cars driving the city

01:39.875 --> 01:41.125
looking for her,
Mother McKeegan.

01:41.208 --> 01:43.166
She's wearing a white robe
and has a bloody nose.

01:43.250 --> 01:44.542
How hard can this be?

01:44.625 --> 01:46.000
You need to hold still,
Mother McKeegan.

01:46.083 --> 01:47.458
-(BABY CRYING)
-You need to work faster.

01:47.542 --> 01:50.500
It'll scar
if it's not done properly.

01:50.583 --> 01:52.250
Do we know
where Emily Dodson is?

01:52.333 --> 01:54.875
There was a lot
of confusion at the cemetery.

01:54.959 --> 01:56.917
(BABY CRYING)

01:57.000 --> 01:59.166
-Elder Seidel?
-No.

01:59.250 --> 02:00.959
(GROANS)

02:01.041 --> 02:03.583
Oh, for heaven's sakes,
bring me the baby.

02:03.667 --> 02:06.583
-(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)
-(MUTTERS)

02:07.375 --> 02:08.417
Okay.

02:09.375 --> 02:10.667
Okay.

02:10.750 --> 02:12.458
Come on. Come on.

02:13.291 --> 02:14.458
Okay.

02:14.542 --> 02:16.583
-(BABY QUIETS)
-(EXHALES)

02:17.625 --> 02:19.250
(SIGHS)

02:21.083 --> 02:22.834
Find Sister.

02:22.917 --> 02:25.166
And get word to Emily Dodson.

02:25.250 --> 02:27.792
(SOFTLY)
Okay. It's okay.

02:31.834 --> 02:33.959
Every mother needs her child.

02:34.583 --> 02:35.583
Hmm?

02:37.959 --> 02:39.208
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

02:41.166 --> 02:43.625
Miss Pitlick gave the okay.

02:43.709 --> 02:47.333
Okay.
I'm gonna bunk in with Hazel.

02:47.417 --> 02:49.792
You can sleep here in my room.

02:51.208 --> 02:54.500
Look, it'll help
with the swelling.

02:55.709 --> 02:58.291
-I don't care about my eye.
-I know.

02:59.542 --> 03:02.458
But just think about
how it will look in court.

03:02.792 --> 03:04.041
In court?

03:04.125 --> 03:07.625
Of course, no, you can't have
the crazy lady looking crazy.

03:10.959 --> 03:14.083
I may have a vanishing cream
and foundation combo

03:14.166 --> 03:15.333
for that shiner.

03:19.792 --> 03:22.792
Where is my son, Miss Street?

03:22.875 --> 03:24.625
What happened to his body?

03:25.542 --> 03:27.750
DELLA STREET:
I don't know, I...

03:30.166 --> 03:31.959
I think...

03:32.041 --> 03:36.375
I think maybe someone,
most likely, moved him.

03:37.667 --> 03:39.375
Long before Easter.

03:40.333 --> 03:43.834
-Long--
-Maybe it'll be a-- a relief...

03:45.166 --> 03:46.750
when they send me to jail.

03:46.834 --> 03:48.834
The trial isn't over.

03:51.792 --> 03:54.458
I know who the jury sees, Della.

03:56.166 --> 03:58.000
What they think of me.

04:00.250 --> 04:02.458
You know, I'd probably think
the same thing.

04:05.542 --> 04:07.333
But I wanted my baby back.

04:10.083 --> 04:11.709
I wanted him back...

04:13.041 --> 04:15.375
more than anything in the world.

04:17.417 --> 04:18.750
I know.

04:25.041 --> 04:27.000
I just wish that you'd known me

04:27.083 --> 04:29.083
sometime before all this.

04:30.792 --> 04:33.041
'Cause I think that
you would say that...

04:35.041 --> 04:37.208
that I was a damn good mother.

04:45.625 --> 04:46.834
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

04:46.917 --> 04:48.959
Do you solemnly swear
that the testimony

04:49.041 --> 04:50.792
you're about to give
will be the truth,

04:50.875 --> 04:52.583
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth,

04:52.667 --> 04:54.709
-so help you God?
-I do.

04:56.000 --> 04:59.250
PERRY MASON:
Detective Ennis.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.417
-You ever killed a man?
-MAYNARD BARNES: Objection.

05:01.500 --> 05:04.166
-Irrelevant. Badgering.
-JUDGE FRED WRIGHT: Sustained.

05:04.250 --> 05:06.333
DETECTIVE ENNIS:
It's okay, Mr. Barnes, Judge.

05:06.417 --> 05:08.917
The answer is yes.
I killed three men

05:09.000 --> 05:11.125
while overseas
serving my country.

05:11.208 --> 05:12.792
You were a soldier in the army?

05:13.792 --> 05:15.166
Just like you, Mr. Mason.

05:15.250 --> 05:17.667
And when you got back,
you got a job as a patrolman

05:17.750 --> 05:19.792
-for the LAPD?
-I believe in service.

05:19.875 --> 05:22.792
MASON: Soldier, cop,
and now detective.

05:22.875 --> 05:25.500
That first kill,
you get 'em with your rifle,
or was it up close?

05:25.583 --> 05:28.333
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Mr. Mason.
-Withdrawn. Withdrawn.

05:28.417 --> 05:31.208
So, you were the first detective
on the scene

05:31.291 --> 05:33.000
the night that Gannon,
Sarecki, and Nowak

05:33.083 --> 05:35.959
delivered Charlie dead
in the arms of my client,
is that correct?

05:36.792 --> 05:37.750
EMILY DODSON:
Charlie!

05:37.834 --> 05:41.125
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:44.208 --> 05:47.166
ENNIS: I was.
I was at my Elks Lodge,

05:47.250 --> 05:49.125
which happens to be
one building over

05:49.208 --> 05:51.166
from where
your client was, uh...

05:51.250 --> 05:52.625
How'd she tell it?

05:53.125 --> 05:54.208
Waiting.

05:54.291 --> 05:55.959
MASON: So you hear the commotion
at your Elks Lodge,

05:56.041 --> 05:57.375
and you go running down
the street

05:57.458 --> 05:59.500
to see if you can help,
which you do.

05:59.583 --> 06:01.792
I'm a cop, uh,
on or off the clock.

06:01.875 --> 06:03.333
Did you nab him in the act?

06:03.417 --> 06:04.750
ENNIS:
The kidnappers were smart.

06:04.834 --> 06:06.208
A busy area,
good escape routes--

06:06.291 --> 06:08.333
Well, how smart could they be?
They were dead the next day.

06:08.417 --> 06:10.125
The location was smart.

06:10.208 --> 06:13.917
And I'm sure your client
did her part to, uh, sell it.

06:14.000 --> 06:15.875
She's a million-dollar weeper,
this one.

06:15.959 --> 06:17.083
(GALLERY WHISPERING)

06:17.166 --> 06:19.125
Your Honor, I ask you
to declare Detective Ennis

06:19.208 --> 06:21.375
-a hostile witness--
-BARNES: Objection, Your Honor.

06:21.458 --> 06:24.208
There's only one hostile man
here.

06:24.291 --> 06:26.583
Case law is clear on this,
Mr. Barnes.

06:26.667 --> 06:29.333
Let the record reflect
that the witness is hostile.

06:29.417 --> 06:31.458
MASON: Thank you, Your Honor.
Detective Ennis,

06:31.542 --> 06:33.125
when the kidnappers met

06:33.208 --> 06:36.542
to divvy up the ransom,
I'm-- I'm curious,

06:36.625 --> 06:40.208
how do you suppose
that George Gannon,

06:40.291 --> 06:43.959
God-fearing,
gun-toting accountant

06:44.041 --> 06:47.834
double-crossed two lifetime
professional hoods?

06:50.667 --> 06:52.583
ENNIS:
Caught them off guard, I'd say.

06:52.667 --> 06:54.250
MASON:
But how did he drive across town

06:54.333 --> 06:57.208
with a bullet in his shoulder
and a busted hip?

06:57.291 --> 06:58.709
Objection, Your Honor.

06:58.792 --> 07:01.500
Oh, my mistake,
(LAUGHS) I'm so sorry.

07:01.583 --> 07:03.000
I got my autopsies confused.

07:03.083 --> 07:05.041
JUDGE WRIGHT:
One more like that, Mr. Mason...

07:05.125 --> 07:07.625
So, Two-Gun Gannon,
back at his bungalow,

07:07.709 --> 07:09.875
regrets the whole thing.

07:09.959 --> 07:13.166
He burns the money
in the fireplace,

07:13.250 --> 07:17.125
types a suicide letter,
sets the letter down,

07:17.208 --> 07:20.333
then he shoots himself
in the head with a shotgun.

07:20.709 --> 07:22.250
Because...

07:22.333 --> 07:24.125
-because what?
-(GUNSHOT)

07:24.208 --> 07:27.458
Because the gun he used
on Sarecki and Nowak
was undignified?

07:27.542 --> 07:30.375
I didn't live in the man's mind.
I just saw the mess he made.

07:30.458 --> 07:32.250
But when you come across
a crime scene like that,

07:32.333 --> 07:34.125
does it remind you
of the six men that you killed?

07:34.208 --> 07:35.625
I said three, not six!

07:35.709 --> 07:37.208
Strike that
from the record, please.

07:37.291 --> 07:40.000
-(GAVEL BANGS)
-Denver, August 1914,

07:40.083 --> 07:41.667
you were working
as a strikebreaker

07:41.750 --> 07:43.875
for a company called
Colorado Fuel and Iron.

07:43.959 --> 07:45.166
You're all over
the place, Mason.

07:45.250 --> 07:47.166
You helped put down workers
at the Ludlow Massacre.

07:47.250 --> 07:49.792
I protected real Americans
who don't like communists.

07:49.875 --> 07:52.667
MASON: This is a list
of senior management
at Colorado Fuel and Iron.

07:52.750 --> 07:55.083
Could you please read out
this name for me, please?

07:55.166 --> 07:57.625
-What name?
-This one right here.

08:02.917 --> 08:06.417
-Eric Q. Seidel.
-Eric Q. Seidel.

08:06.500 --> 08:10.166
Senior VP of Colorado
Fuel and Iron, and currently

08:10.250 --> 08:14.333
elder in charge of finances
at the Radiant Assembly of God,

08:14.417 --> 08:16.333
and George Gannon's boss.

08:16.417 --> 08:20.709
I have two witnesses
that put Sarecki and Nowak

08:20.792 --> 08:22.166
in Denver as well.

08:22.250 --> 08:26.709
All four in the same place
at the same time.

08:26.792 --> 08:30.834
So tell me, Detective Ennis,
how was the Los Angeles reunion?

08:30.917 --> 08:32.875
-Objection! Argumentative.
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Sustained.

08:32.959 --> 08:34.834
MASON:
We have two further eyewitnesses

08:34.917 --> 08:36.709
that place you
at a Chinatown brothel,

08:36.792 --> 08:39.875
picking up a prostitute
by the name of Tang Yin,

08:39.959 --> 08:42.458
driving her to an auto court
in Newhall

08:42.542 --> 08:44.542
for the sole purpose

08:44.625 --> 08:47.542
of nursing Charlie Dodson.

08:47.625 --> 08:51.625
The tragedy is, this young lady
is so high on heroin,

08:51.709 --> 08:54.583
Charlie asphyxiated
on her poisoned milk.

08:54.667 --> 08:57.041
-Come on. This is ridiculous!
-MASON: This is an affidavit

08:57.125 --> 08:59.792
from a private investigator
by the name of Pete Strickland.

08:59.875 --> 09:01.875
Puts you at the same brothel,

09:01.959 --> 09:05.834
the same night that Tang Yin
suddenly overdosed.

09:11.834 --> 09:15.166
And then your old pal,
Eric Q. Seidel,

09:15.250 --> 09:19.458
suddenly disappears
just as he is set to testify

09:20.250 --> 09:22.709
about financial irregularities

09:22.792 --> 09:25.792
at the Radiant Assembly of God.

09:25.875 --> 09:31.667
Sarecki, Nowak, Gannon,
Eric Seidel, Tang Yin,

09:32.250 --> 09:33.959
Charlie Dodson.

09:34.041 --> 09:36.917
And the one person
who connects them all

09:37.000 --> 09:40.500
is Detective Joseph Ennis.

09:41.458 --> 09:43.750
(GALLERY MURMURING)

09:43.834 --> 09:45.417
It won't work, Mason.

09:45.500 --> 09:48.041
-You kidnapped Charlie Dodson.
-HAMILTON BURGER:
He's not gonna confess.

09:48.125 --> 09:49.458
You stood over his body
and you said,

09:49.542 --> 09:51.583
"Now, let's just sew up his eyes
and get the cash!"

09:51.667 --> 09:54.542
-The kid was already dead!
-He's not gonna confess!

09:54.625 --> 09:55.792
I'm not done yet!

09:55.875 --> 09:58.417
BURGER: No one confesses
on the stand.

09:58.500 --> 10:01.709
There's a reason
why Barnes didn't call him!

10:01.792 --> 10:05.083
No one ever confesses
on the stand.

10:05.166 --> 10:07.917
Oh, my God.
All right. Okay.

10:08.000 --> 10:10.166
Even if I come up short, I can
make a circumstantial case.

10:10.250 --> 10:12.458
How many of those exhibits
that you were waving around

10:12.542 --> 10:13.792
are legitimate?

10:13.875 --> 10:15.542
-Uh...
-Della?

10:15.625 --> 10:17.667
He made up one of them
and fudged two.

10:17.750 --> 10:19.000
BURGER: Mm-hmm.

10:19.083 --> 10:21.875
And Judge Wright is not going
to let you turn Ennis hostile,

10:21.959 --> 10:24.125
or let you get away with half
of that bullshit

10:24.208 --> 10:25.208
that you just tried.

10:25.291 --> 10:28.333
Maybe don't bring up
the second autopsy.

10:28.417 --> 10:30.166
Did you feel like
you're about to break?

10:30.250 --> 10:31.333
-No.
-No?

10:31.417 --> 10:34.333
You were drowning.
I threw you a water donut.

10:34.417 --> 10:35.917
BURGER:
Rest the case.

10:39.375 --> 10:40.417
What?

10:40.500 --> 10:43.291
You've got the jury
thinking about the hundred grand

10:43.375 --> 10:45.166
that the church needed
for their loan.

10:45.250 --> 10:46.959
Introduce the general ledger
that shows

10:47.041 --> 10:50.083
they got close to
a hundred grand in "donations"

10:50.166 --> 10:53.083
around the time
that the ransom note was left.

10:53.166 --> 10:55.000
Call no one else.

10:55.083 --> 10:56.458
That is gutless.

10:56.542 --> 10:58.333
That's reasonable doubt.

10:58.417 --> 11:00.834
Oh, my God. All right. Okay.
Look, I know

11:00.917 --> 11:03.458
we've all had a particularly
fucked up Easter Sunday.

11:03.542 --> 11:05.834
-(DELLA CLEARS THROAT)
-MASON: Almost killed
in a near riot.

11:05.917 --> 11:07.333
We're in court tomorrow.

11:07.417 --> 11:11.667
He is a detective
that has killed the witnesses

11:11.750 --> 11:13.875
that can finger him
for the same crime

11:13.959 --> 11:16.583
he himself is investigating!

11:16.667 --> 11:18.667
We have to go after him!

11:21.250 --> 11:22.875
Come on!

11:22.959 --> 11:25.500
(SIGHS) I-- (GROANS)

11:25.583 --> 11:28.542
Well, I guess you could...

11:28.625 --> 11:30.667
introduce the Denver affidavits,

11:30.750 --> 11:34.041
the one from Sister Alice
refuting the jail matron.

11:34.125 --> 11:35.709
But then you'd have
to get Barnes

11:35.792 --> 11:38.208
to stipulate to admissibility,
which he won't do.

11:38.291 --> 11:40.166
Then, you'd have
to call Sister Alice.

11:40.250 --> 11:41.750
You could call Emily.

11:44.917 --> 11:46.291
Yeah, let's do that.

11:46.375 --> 11:48.208
Let's call the woman
who just signed over

11:48.291 --> 11:49.500
her infant's rotting body

11:49.583 --> 11:51.166
to Our Sister
of the Stolen Nurse's Outfit

11:51.250 --> 11:54.500
so we could put her on a plate
for Barnes to gobble
the fuck up!

11:54.583 --> 11:56.417
Let's absolutely do that.

11:56.500 --> 11:59.041
-All respects, Della...
-(SIGHS)

11:59.125 --> 12:01.250
...I would call Ennis
before I'd call Emily.

12:01.333 --> 12:02.959
And that's exactly
what I'm gonna do.

12:03.041 --> 12:06.291
And since there's no more air
to breathe

12:06.375 --> 12:09.834
with his ego in the room,
I bid you all a good night.

12:16.166 --> 12:17.291
He's right.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.375
You don't go in
unless you got him.

12:21.458 --> 12:23.208
And you really don't got him.

12:25.834 --> 12:29.542
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

13:00.834 --> 13:02.667
DELLA:
You've been out here for ages.

13:02.750 --> 13:05.166
MASON: (GROANS)
I'm trying to clear my head.

13:05.250 --> 13:06.500
DELLA:
Is it working?

13:07.375 --> 13:08.917
MASON:
Well, not with you talking.

13:13.291 --> 13:16.125
I think you should put Emily
on the stand.

13:18.083 --> 13:19.333
She deserves a chance to--

13:19.417 --> 13:21.333
MASON:
She deserves to walk free,

13:21.417 --> 13:23.375
hopefully, into a clean,
well-lit asylum.

13:23.458 --> 13:25.750
DELLA: She's as clear-headed
as I've ever seen her.

13:26.959 --> 13:30.250
A little raw from the riot,
but she wants to be heard.

13:30.333 --> 13:31.375
(SCOFFS)

13:32.750 --> 13:35.291
Your arrogant prick friend
Burger is right.

13:35.375 --> 13:39.625
I am gonna rest the case.
We don't have Ennis.

13:39.709 --> 13:42.000
He will deny everything.
I'll just look desperate.

13:42.083 --> 13:43.875
So I'm just gonna stand
in front of Barnes

13:43.959 --> 13:46.500
and that fucking dinosaur judge
and say, "You know what?

13:46.583 --> 13:48.709
I give up. Let's just hang her
and go home for dinner."

13:48.792 --> 13:50.250
I tried prepping her.

13:52.417 --> 13:54.875
You did w--
you-- you tried to prep her?

13:55.000 --> 13:57.500
We talked. She's ready.

13:58.792 --> 14:00.375
She's ready to take the stand.

14:00.458 --> 14:02.208
MASON: Did you and Hazel
hash this one out?

14:02.291 --> 14:05.542
-No. (SCOFFS)
-Is this the collective
wisdom of the coven?

14:05.625 --> 14:09.041
I have watched a parade of men
get up there and demean her.

14:09.125 --> 14:11.583
-Ask the right questions,
and they'll see through it.
-That's what this is.

14:11.667 --> 14:13.709
-Oh, that's what this is about.
-They'll give her a chance.

14:13.792 --> 14:16.500
This is just a crusade for you.
And what? Emily's what?
Your proxy?

14:16.583 --> 14:18.250
No, that is not
what I meant, Perry.

14:18.333 --> 14:20.709
Yes, it is, because you see
a woman being "demeaned by men,"

14:20.792 --> 14:22.875
you think it's about you.
Guess what? It's not.

14:22.959 --> 14:25.417
And I'm sorry to be the one to
break this to you, sweetheart,

14:25.500 --> 14:27.542
but padding around
your little boarding house

14:27.625 --> 14:29.208
with your little
hand model girlfriend

14:29.291 --> 14:32.333
isn't the same as being framed
for killing your fucking kid.

14:42.959 --> 14:44.834
You didn't think
I knew about Hazel?

14:48.792 --> 14:50.208
I figured you knew.

14:52.834 --> 14:56.166
I just didn't think you'd
throw it in my face like that.

15:06.083 --> 15:08.166
I'll type up
the questions for you,

15:08.250 --> 15:10.500
in case you wake up
and realize...

15:11.625 --> 15:13.125
I'm right.

15:26.291 --> 15:27.542
(EXHALES)

15:29.166 --> 15:30.792
PAUL DRAKE: Ain't gonna be
too much longer.

15:30.875 --> 15:33.458
CLARA DRAKE: The newspaper here
made it sound pretty bad

15:33.542 --> 15:34.875
for your white lady.

15:35.959 --> 15:37.750
If you know, why'd you ask?

15:37.834 --> 15:40.291
CLARA: 'Cause I wanna know
what you think about it.

15:40.375 --> 15:42.542
I'm just trying to see
this thing through.

15:42.625 --> 15:45.208
CLARA: And I'm trying
to figure out where my home is.

15:45.291 --> 15:47.166
Enough, Clara, enough of that.

15:48.041 --> 15:49.667
This man, Ennis,
you don't understand,

15:49.750 --> 15:51.709
if he wants you gone,
you're gone.

15:53.250 --> 15:57.166
I had to keep you safe,
keep our child safe.

15:58.667 --> 16:00.834
CLARA: Well, I hope
it was worth it.

16:02.583 --> 16:03.583
Yeah.

16:05.417 --> 16:06.792
I love you, babe.

16:08.125 --> 16:09.583
CLARA:
Night.

16:10.542 --> 16:14.041
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:22.917 --> 16:25.709
So the kid snuffed it
sucking a milkmaid's tit?

16:27.750 --> 16:28.917
Yeah.

16:30.625 --> 16:32.417
-And the hooker's dead?
-Mm-hmm.

16:32.500 --> 16:34.625
-And Seidel's what?
-Seidel's dead.

16:36.750 --> 16:37.917
Yeah, probably.

16:41.625 --> 16:43.125
We were slow.

16:43.917 --> 16:45.250
And he was smart.

16:45.333 --> 16:49.208
-I'm just about out of moves.
-Don't sound much like you.

16:49.291 --> 16:53.709
Yeah, well, that's the fuck
of this lawyering thing.

16:53.792 --> 16:55.875
You can have all the truth
on your side,

16:55.959 --> 16:57.917
but if you can't prove it,

16:58.000 --> 17:00.458
if you can't hold it
in your hand,

17:00.542 --> 17:01.959
it don't exist.

17:04.417 --> 17:06.291
You said "just about"
out of moves.

17:08.709 --> 17:10.291
(SIGHS) Yeah.

17:12.333 --> 17:15.625
Well, seems like you got this
hotshot negro investigator now.

17:15.709 --> 17:17.375
Don't see why
you don't put him on it.

17:17.458 --> 17:19.250
He can't do it.

17:19.333 --> 17:21.500
And there's nobody else
I can ask.

17:23.333 --> 17:25.709
So you're just gonna race past
an apology, huh?

17:27.500 --> 17:30.792
-"Do me this one, Strick."
-I know you've been busting ass.

17:33.333 --> 17:35.417
I ain't been myself.

17:35.500 --> 17:37.542
Or maybe this is just you
in a suit.

17:41.083 --> 17:43.834
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:43.917 --> 17:45.291
(SIGHS)

17:47.125 --> 17:48.458
So, what's the move?

17:54.625 --> 17:57.041
Dinner's been on the table
for half an hour now.

17:57.125 --> 17:59.583
MATTHEW DODSON:
I'm not keeping you from it.

17:59.667 --> 18:01.417
It is the day after Christmas.

18:01.500 --> 18:03.417
-I don't understand.
-That's right.
That's right, Emily.

18:03.500 --> 18:05.667
It's the day after Christmas.
It's a regular day

18:05.750 --> 18:08.083
with regular things that have
to be done at the store, okay?

18:08.166 --> 18:09.959
Okay. I'll--
I'll put a plate in the oven.

18:10.041 --> 18:12.000
No, put it in the fridge.
I'm gonna be home late.

18:12.083 --> 18:13.375
EMILY: How late?

18:13.458 --> 18:15.709
♪ ("HEIGH-HO,
EVERYBODY, HEIGH-HO"
BY RUDY VALLÉE PLAYING)

18:15.792 --> 18:17.375
♪ So I'll just begin it... ♪

18:17.458 --> 18:19.959
Yeah,
it's just us chickens tonight.

18:20.041 --> 18:22.959
♪ Heigh-ho, everybody
Heigh-ho ♪

18:23.041 --> 18:24.542
(PLATE SHATTERS)

18:25.083 --> 18:26.458
Fuck.

18:26.542 --> 18:28.542
♪ ("LIFE IS JUST
A BOWL OF CHERRIES"
BY RUDY VALLÉE PLAYING) ♪

18:28.625 --> 18:29.959
(COOING)

18:30.041 --> 18:33.792
EMILY: Hmm. (CHUCKLES)

18:33.875 --> 18:37.333
♪ You work, you save
You worry so ♪

18:37.417 --> 18:39.458
♪ But you can't
Take your dough ♪

18:39.542 --> 18:41.750
-♪ When you go, go, go ♪
-♪ Go, go ♪

18:41.834 --> 18:45.291
(SINGING ALONG)
♪ Life is just a bowl
Of cherries ♪

18:45.375 --> 18:49.500
♪ So live and laugh at it all ♪

18:49.583 --> 18:51.291
(CHARLIE COOING)

18:51.375 --> 18:55.208
(WHISTLES, CHUCKLES)

18:56.291 --> 18:58.166
-(CHARLIE BLOWS RASPBERRIES)
-(CHUCKLES)

18:58.250 --> 19:02.458
(SOFTLY) And the turtle keeps
a shell on his back

19:02.542 --> 19:05.250
so wherever he goes, he's home.

19:07.417 --> 19:09.542
(SMACKS LIPS) Yes.

19:09.625 --> 19:11.709
But who loves you more?

19:12.709 --> 19:15.417
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

19:22.375 --> 19:25.083
(RINGING CONTINUES)

19:25.166 --> 19:28.250
MASON: And that was
George calling you?

19:30.125 --> 19:31.250
Yes.

19:33.125 --> 19:35.625
What did he say to you
on that call?

19:38.333 --> 19:40.208
EMILY: He told me
how much he missed me,

19:40.291 --> 19:41.667
how much he loved me.

19:43.792 --> 19:44.917
I mean, you--

19:45.792 --> 19:48.000
you gotta understand,
my husband--

19:48.083 --> 19:49.291
Objection. Narrative.

19:49.375 --> 19:51.792
You-- you'll get your chance
in a hot minute.

19:52.458 --> 19:54.625
I'm-- I'm sorry, Judge?

19:57.458 --> 19:59.667
Thank you. I'm sorry.

19:59.750 --> 20:02.917
You-- you were--
you were saying your husband...

20:05.375 --> 20:08.291
My husband was gone
all the time,

20:08.959 --> 20:11.125
and when he wasn't...

20:12.000 --> 20:13.166
he was...

20:15.208 --> 20:16.917
unkind.

20:17.000 --> 20:18.750
He was the only man
I'd ever known,

20:18.834 --> 20:20.500
and so I always thought that...

20:21.291 --> 20:23.458
this was the way
of man and wife.

20:25.000 --> 20:27.250
But with George, I...

20:27.333 --> 20:29.625
I felt as though I were...

20:31.542 --> 20:34.333
a... a person.

20:38.667 --> 20:40.041
And now, you know...

20:41.875 --> 20:43.917
It was all a lie.

20:44.000 --> 20:45.959
EMILY: Will you tell me
that joke again?

20:46.041 --> 20:48.041
(GIGGLES) Knock, knock.

20:48.125 --> 20:51.291
He kept me on that phone
for over an hour that night.

20:51.375 --> 20:53.166
(LAUGHS)

20:54.542 --> 20:56.542
George...
(LAUGHS)

20:58.375 --> 21:01.208
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

21:03.291 --> 21:05.375
And he told me he loved me...

21:06.792 --> 21:08.959
while they broke into my home

21:09.041 --> 21:12.000
and stole my son.

21:13.834 --> 21:16.375
(MURMURING)

21:22.166 --> 21:23.709
This is my last question.

21:26.333 --> 21:28.041
(SIGHS)

21:29.458 --> 21:31.250
Emily, did you have
anything to do

21:31.333 --> 21:32.875
with your son's kidnapping?

21:42.208 --> 21:44.792
I've realized, Mr. Mason,

21:44.875 --> 21:48.542
that I have only had one love
in my life,

21:50.208 --> 21:52.083
and it wasn't Matthew.

21:53.917 --> 21:55.458
It wasn't George.

22:00.166 --> 22:01.208
It...

22:04.417 --> 22:06.750
(VOICE BREAKING)
...was my son.

22:08.917 --> 22:10.041
He was...

22:12.709 --> 22:14.250
my heart.

22:17.458 --> 22:20.625
So, no, I had nothing to do
with his kidnapping.

22:26.125 --> 22:27.166
Thank you.

22:29.667 --> 22:31.291
Nothing further, Your Honor.

22:32.125 --> 22:33.458
Thank you, Emily.

22:35.959 --> 22:38.667
BARNES:
"Take me away, George,

22:39.458 --> 22:41.250
to some island in the ocean,

22:41.333 --> 22:44.959
and set fire to the boat
that got us there."

22:47.417 --> 22:50.542
I said a lot of stupid things
in those letters.

22:50.625 --> 22:52.625
A more accurate account
would have been,

22:52.709 --> 22:54.875
"Take me away, George,
to the Star Motel

22:54.959 --> 22:58.083
where we can have sex
and I can abandon my boy."

22:58.166 --> 22:59.917
-Objection!
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Sustained.

23:00.000 --> 23:01.583
-(GALLERY WHISPERING)
-BARNES: Quite right.

23:01.667 --> 23:05.000
It was objected to
because it is objectionable.

23:05.083 --> 23:08.917
A married woman fornicating
with her lover in one room,

23:09.000 --> 23:12.667
while her infant boy,
the only love of her life,

23:12.750 --> 23:14.083
cried out from behind a wall.

23:14.166 --> 23:15.625
Is there a question here, Judge?

23:15.709 --> 23:17.375
BARNES: Yes.

23:17.458 --> 23:21.041
When you weren't having sex
with George Gannon in motels,

23:21.125 --> 23:23.959
did you tell him about
your husband's money,

23:24.041 --> 23:25.333
Mrs. Dodson?

23:26.208 --> 23:28.709
No. We--
we never talked about money.

23:28.792 --> 23:31.709
Yeah, but you told him Matthew
was Herman Baggerly's son.

23:31.792 --> 23:35.959
And from that he understood
Matthew had access to money.

23:36.041 --> 23:37.500
Well, I didn't think--

23:38.417 --> 23:40.291
-I didn't realize--
-Mrs. Dodson,

23:40.375 --> 23:42.959
isn't it true
that if George Gannon

23:43.041 --> 23:45.625
hadn't known those facts
about Matthew,

23:45.709 --> 23:49.875
he never would have come up
with his plan to hurt Charlie?

23:52.417 --> 23:55.500
I-- I don't--
I don't understand.

23:55.583 --> 23:58.667
Mrs. Dodson, if it hadn't been
for your affair,

23:58.750 --> 24:01.375
there never would have been
a kidnapping.

24:02.000 --> 24:05.000
(GALLERY MURMURING)

24:07.291 --> 24:09.208
Yes, I suppose that is true.

24:09.291 --> 24:11.792
BARNES: Yes, you abandoned
Charlie in his room

24:11.875 --> 24:14.125
to answer the phone call
from your lover George,

24:14.208 --> 24:19.250
just as you abandoned him
to have sex at the Star Motel.

24:19.333 --> 24:21.959
Did you not fail to prevent
the perpetrators

24:22.041 --> 24:24.875
from taking Charlie away,
Mrs. Dodson?

24:24.959 --> 24:26.625
He called to distract me.

24:26.709 --> 24:30.542
You failed to stop them,
yes or no?

24:30.625 --> 24:33.917
-Yes, but--
-Yes. You wanted
to get your baby out of the way

24:34.000 --> 24:36.750
so you could run away
with this kind man

24:36.834 --> 24:39.166
who made you feel like a person.

24:39.250 --> 24:40.166
EMILY: Stop.

24:40.250 --> 24:42.875
BARNES: Run away
to an island in the ocean

24:42.959 --> 24:46.834
and set fire to the boat
that got you there.

24:46.917 --> 24:48.875
-Objection! Badgering!
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Sustained.

24:48.959 --> 24:51.000
BARNES: You whispered "guilty"
at the arraignment.

24:51.083 --> 24:52.709
You confessed at the jailhouse.

24:52.792 --> 24:54.959
Why don't you make it official
for the record?

24:55.041 --> 24:56.250
-Objection!
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Mr. Barnes!

24:56.333 --> 24:58.667
-Please stop, sir.
Please. Please.
-(GAVEL BANGS)

24:58.750 --> 25:00.083
(GALLERY MURMURING)

25:00.166 --> 25:03.458
Isn't it your fault
Charlie's dead?

25:04.417 --> 25:07.417
Isn't it true, Mrs. Dodson,

25:07.500 --> 25:09.709
that if it hadn't been
for your actions,

25:09.792 --> 25:13.500
your perfect Charlie boy
would still be alive?

25:13.583 --> 25:15.583
(GALLERY MURMURING)

25:20.750 --> 25:24.458
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

25:27.625 --> 25:28.792
Yes.

25:29.875 --> 25:30.959
Yes.

25:34.709 --> 25:38.000
Well,
no more tears for your boy?

25:42.834 --> 25:44.333
All cried out.

25:47.208 --> 25:48.208
Hmm.

25:57.834 --> 26:00.000
You may be excused, Mrs. Dodson.

26:04.166 --> 26:07.500
Bailiff, will you kindly help
Mrs. Dodson?

26:07.583 --> 26:11.542
-♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(FLASH BULBS POP)

26:16.959 --> 26:20.208
(INDISTINCT CLAMORING)

26:30.250 --> 26:32.917
(CLAMORING CONTINUES)

26:52.125 --> 26:54.000
(CLAMORING FADES)

26:54.083 --> 26:56.542
ENNIS: Quite a show
you put on today, Mason.

26:57.792 --> 26:59.166
Real heart-tugger.

27:00.875 --> 27:04.417
Almost made me feel sorry
for the murdering little snipe.

27:04.500 --> 27:07.083
You and I both know
she's innocent.

27:08.417 --> 27:09.417
Do we?

27:10.625 --> 27:13.834
Gene, ain't he said
something in his opening

27:13.917 --> 27:16.500
about catching Charlie's killer?

27:16.583 --> 27:18.250
(CHUCKLES)

27:18.333 --> 27:20.125
(GRUNTS)

27:20.208 --> 27:22.000
DETECTIVE HOLCOMB:
You come at my partner again,

27:22.083 --> 27:25.625
they'll find your rat-chewed
carcass floating in the sewers.

27:25.709 --> 27:26.917
You got me?

27:27.000 --> 27:28.375
Gene, come on.

27:31.083 --> 27:32.667
See you at the hanging.

27:32.750 --> 27:35.792
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:47.583 --> 27:50.125
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

27:58.333 --> 28:04.166
(MUTTERING) Phone call. Barbara.
Charlie photo. Ransom note.

28:04.250 --> 28:05.875
No, ransom note should be first.

28:05.959 --> 28:08.417
Seven thousand on top
of your debt I paid,

28:09.291 --> 28:12.834
and my last bottle of mescal...

28:14.041 --> 28:15.917
-for the bad timing.
-I'm busy.

28:17.041 --> 28:18.458
It's a fair price.

28:19.667 --> 28:21.333
It's a fair price
and then some, papi.

28:21.417 --> 28:23.709
I'm gonna file a motion
to stay on your sales contract.

28:23.792 --> 28:25.291
A motion to delay your closing.

28:25.375 --> 28:27.583
And a motion to cure
your title defects.

28:28.625 --> 28:31.500
I'm a lawyer now.
So I'll see you in court.

28:31.583 --> 28:32.709
Just take the money.

28:32.792 --> 28:34.458
Well, that would
constitute an agreement,

28:34.542 --> 28:36.166
so why don't you fuck off?

28:40.166 --> 28:41.166
(SIGHS)

28:42.834 --> 28:45.709
MASON: Phone call.
Barbara. Charlie photo.

28:47.083 --> 28:49.583
There are thirty airfields
in Los Angeles right now.

28:49.667 --> 28:51.583
When this prohibition shit
is over,

28:51.667 --> 28:53.542
there's only gonna be
five of them left.

28:53.625 --> 28:56.291
I'm a wetback and a woman.

28:58.500 --> 29:01.166
I need to stay ahead
of the rest of them.

29:01.250 --> 29:03.000
(SIGHS)

29:04.250 --> 29:07.667
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

29:15.542 --> 29:18.709
(MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

29:19.333 --> 29:21.041
Here we go. (SIGHS)

29:24.583 --> 29:26.500
Anyone want any more peas?

29:26.583 --> 29:28.041
I'll take some.

29:31.834 --> 29:33.875
DELLA:
The peas are wonderful, June.

29:33.959 --> 29:37.667
JUNE PITLICK:
The man at the market wanted
to sell me some old cans,

29:37.750 --> 29:40.041
but I knew better.

29:40.125 --> 29:42.375
These are from the new cans.

29:46.166 --> 29:48.542
Did Mr. Mason say
I did good today?

29:50.041 --> 29:52.291
He thought you did incredible.

29:52.375 --> 29:53.917
You shined up there.

30:06.250 --> 30:10.083
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

30:22.041 --> 30:27.041
In conclusion, gentlemen
and ladies of the jury...

30:28.208 --> 30:29.834
Um...

30:29.917 --> 30:33.208
Yeah. To--
In summation-- In s--

30:34.917 --> 30:37.625
To conclude, ladies
and gentlemen of the jury,

30:38.583 --> 30:40.917
Mr. Barnes--
Mr. Barnes tricked you--

30:41.000 --> 30:43.291
Mr. Barnes has tricked you,
sleight of hand.

30:43.375 --> 30:44.917
He made you look--

30:45.750 --> 30:47.458
It was sleight of hand--

30:49.083 --> 30:51.041
Mr. Barnes has made
you look at Emily,

30:51.125 --> 30:53.250
when what
you should be looking at...

30:55.625 --> 30:56.667
(EXHALES)

30:58.375 --> 31:02.208
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury, to conclude--

31:02.291 --> 31:07.000
In conclusion,
it's all inconclusive.

31:15.125 --> 31:16.875
(EXHALES)

31:16.959 --> 31:18.834
I'm sorry, Charlie boy.

31:20.250 --> 31:21.625
I can't do it.

31:25.041 --> 31:28.834
Charlie Dodson...

31:46.917 --> 31:48.500
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

31:48.583 --> 31:53.458
On the 26th of December, 1931,
the day after Christmas,

31:54.458 --> 31:57.041
a man broke
into Emily Dodson's home

31:57.125 --> 31:58.625
and took her child.

31:59.417 --> 32:01.709
We all know what happened next.

32:08.417 --> 32:09.750
I took this photograph

32:09.834 --> 32:14.041
when I was then
an investigator on this case.

32:15.250 --> 32:18.709
And I stood over
Charlie Dodson's body in...

32:19.375 --> 32:20.834
disbelief.

32:23.041 --> 32:25.875
Because little boys
who look like this...

32:28.208 --> 32:30.041
shouldn't end up like this.

32:30.875 --> 32:33.208
(MURMURING)

32:36.000 --> 32:37.375
So what do we do...

32:38.500 --> 32:41.875
when something
as horrific as this happens?

32:43.917 --> 32:46.291
Because we have to do
something, right?

32:46.375 --> 32:50.583
We have to be able to feel
that we can fix this.

32:51.917 --> 32:52.959
So here we are.

32:54.417 --> 32:56.250
You, the jury,
me, now the lawyer,

32:56.333 --> 32:59.709
and all of us wanting
desperately to fix this.

33:01.083 --> 33:02.709
When I took this photograph--

33:04.458 --> 33:06.959
I have never wanted
anything more

33:07.041 --> 33:09.083
than to find those
who are responsible

33:09.583 --> 33:10.875
and make them pay.

33:12.417 --> 33:17.333
I wanted--
I wanted vengeance for Charlie.

33:17.417 --> 33:20.542
And I wanted to take that act
of vengeance into my own hands.

33:20.625 --> 33:21.792
I still do.

33:21.875 --> 33:25.417
And I think-- I-- I-- I hope,

33:25.500 --> 33:27.583
after standing in front of you
all these weeks,

33:28.291 --> 33:29.917
you know how I felt...

33:32.166 --> 33:33.417
how I feel.

33:37.125 --> 33:39.625
But here's something maybe
you don't know.

33:41.709 --> 33:45.542
If I thought for one second,
truthfully,

33:45.625 --> 33:47.417
that Emily Dodson was guilty,

33:48.458 --> 33:50.542
I would walk her
to the gallows myself.

33:50.625 --> 33:53.750
If I thought
that was the way to fix it,

33:53.834 --> 33:57.208
I would have no choice,
because I now stand for the law.

33:57.291 --> 33:59.500
And the law tells me,
if you are guilty,

33:59.583 --> 34:02.166
you must pay for your crime.

34:02.250 --> 34:05.291
Emily Dodson is innocent.

34:05.375 --> 34:09.291
-(TYPEWRITER CLACKING)
-The District Attorney
has done a great job--

34:09.375 --> 34:13.375
a great job of playing
to your passions,

34:13.458 --> 34:15.417
tapping in your desire
for vengeance--

34:15.500 --> 34:18.875
I'm sorry. Our.
Our desire for vengeance.

34:18.959 --> 34:22.000
He's raised public outcry,
and then...

34:24.166 --> 34:29.000
he has attacked
this woman at every turn.

34:31.291 --> 34:32.500
For what?

34:33.834 --> 34:35.709
For having an affair?

34:35.792 --> 34:38.917
Did he prove that Emily
had anything to do with the plot

34:39.000 --> 34:41.333
to kidnap Charlie? No.

34:41.417 --> 34:43.041
Did he prove that Emily
had anything to do

34:43.125 --> 34:46.000
with Charlie's murder,
the murder of her own son?

34:47.417 --> 34:48.750
No, he did not.

34:48.834 --> 34:51.458
The truth is he did not,

34:51.542 --> 34:55.291
because the truth
is she did not.

34:55.375 --> 34:57.709
And the District Attorney
knows this.

34:57.792 --> 35:00.625
And so he attacks her
because he cannot attack

35:00.709 --> 35:04.041
the truth that
Emily Dodson is innocent.

35:10.291 --> 35:12.709
Written above Judge Wright here

35:12.792 --> 35:15.208
are the commandments
of this court.

35:15.291 --> 35:19.291
"Find truth, seek justice,"
in that order,

35:19.375 --> 35:24.667
because you cannot seek justice
without first knowing the truth.

35:25.542 --> 35:29.458
And if the truth is hidden
or obscured

35:29.542 --> 35:32.750
by distraction or lies,

35:32.834 --> 35:36.500
you'll never find justice,
you'll never achieve justice,

35:36.583 --> 35:38.500
and therefore...

35:38.583 --> 35:42.208
you will never fix
what happened to Charlie Dodson.

35:47.667 --> 35:50.166
I stood in that morgue
on New Year's Eve,

35:50.250 --> 35:51.792
and I wanted blood.

35:53.875 --> 35:55.875
But I stand here today
for the law,

35:55.959 --> 35:59.417
and the law tells me
I have to be better than that.

36:00.959 --> 36:04.083
We all have to be
better than that

36:04.166 --> 36:08.417
because a woman's life
is at stake.

36:11.583 --> 36:15.375
And on the 26th
of December, 1931,

36:15.458 --> 36:16.750
the day after Christmas,

36:16.834 --> 36:20.291
a man broke into her home
and took her son.

36:22.875 --> 36:24.291
He took her heart...

36:26.875 --> 36:28.750
and she'll never get that back.

36:30.083 --> 36:31.500
That's the truth.

36:36.291 --> 36:37.625
All I ask...

36:39.417 --> 36:42.542
is that you are as courageous...

36:42.625 --> 36:45.792
as you are honest
in seeking justice.

36:47.959 --> 36:49.000
Thank you.

36:53.667 --> 36:56.041
(GALLERY MURMURING)

37:02.333 --> 37:05.041
The truth, Mr. Mason?

37:05.125 --> 37:06.500
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:06.583 --> 37:08.917
Ladies and gentlemen,
the truth is...

37:09.000 --> 37:11.959
that woman had sex
with Charlie's kidnapper

37:12.041 --> 37:15.917
and left her baby
crying in the next room.

37:16.000 --> 37:19.583
The truth is she was arrested
for these crimes,

37:19.667 --> 37:22.208
and the truth, Mr. Mason, is...

37:22.291 --> 37:25.083
(SCOFFS)
...she confessed to them.

37:25.166 --> 37:28.083
So, yes, please,
ladies and gentlemen,

37:28.166 --> 37:32.750
be honest and courageous
in seeking justice

37:32.834 --> 37:34.709
and find that woman...

37:37.041 --> 37:38.125
guilty.

37:38.208 --> 37:41.041
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:06.875 --> 38:08.083
(GROANS)

38:10.834 --> 38:14.125
-It's not your job to feed me.
-Oh, I know.

38:14.208 --> 38:17.083
It was an entirely
humanitarian impulse.

38:17.709 --> 38:19.250
(SCOFFS)

38:20.875 --> 38:22.125
(SIGHS)

38:22.208 --> 38:25.208
You haven't moved for hours.
Thoughts?

38:29.041 --> 38:31.917
I'm thinking Barnes
did some damage with Emily.

38:32.834 --> 38:33.917
True.

38:35.375 --> 38:37.000
But we might not have
made day three

38:37.083 --> 38:39.083
if we hadn't put her
on the stand.

38:46.083 --> 38:47.417
(SIGHS)

38:47.500 --> 38:49.458
I want to apologize
for the other night.

38:49.542 --> 38:50.792
DELLA: No, don't.

38:50.875 --> 38:52.500
If we're gonna be
working together,

38:52.583 --> 38:56.208
we need to be people who can act
abominably on occasion.

38:57.417 --> 39:00.792
You...
you wanna do more of this?

39:00.875 --> 39:03.667
I prefer having a job
to the alternative.

39:06.458 --> 39:09.166
I like Hazel. A lot.

39:11.959 --> 39:15.750
She's a pip.
And it's none of your business.

39:16.417 --> 39:17.625
(DOOR OPENS)

39:20.667 --> 39:22.792
-Jury's done for the night.
-(MASON SIGHS)

39:23.583 --> 39:26.417
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

39:26.500 --> 39:30.166
Three days.
You think it's a good sign?

39:31.917 --> 39:34.375
E.B. would say...

39:34.458 --> 39:36.834
(IMITATING E.B.)
"I'd rather be us than them."

39:36.917 --> 39:38.792
(CHUCKLES)

39:39.667 --> 39:41.959
I think it's more...
(CLEARS THROAT)

39:43.291 --> 39:45.166
(IMITATING E.B.)
"I'd rather be us than them."

39:45.250 --> 39:47.041
(LAUGHS)

39:47.500 --> 39:48.792
MASON: Hmm.

39:51.000 --> 39:52.792
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

39:52.875 --> 39:54.375
Where the fuck
have you been?

39:54.458 --> 39:56.417
Chasing chocolate
Easter bunnies?

39:56.500 --> 39:58.458
Had me some sick days coming.

39:58.542 --> 40:01.250
You missed five goddamn
shifts this week, Drake.

40:01.333 --> 40:03.500
Had some things to do, Joe.

40:04.500 --> 40:06.250
Joe? Who you calling Joe?

40:06.333 --> 40:08.333
And why the fuck
ain't you in uniform?

40:08.417 --> 40:11.667
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

40:26.333 --> 40:28.583
(GALLERY MURMURING)

40:31.333 --> 40:32.583
(INAUDIBLE)

40:36.375 --> 40:37.834
(DOOR OPENS)

40:37.917 --> 40:39.667
BAILIFF: All rise.

40:44.875 --> 40:47.583
The People versus Emily Dodson
is back in session.

40:47.667 --> 40:49.834
The Honorable Judge Wright
presiding.

40:50.709 --> 40:52.417
Judge, all jurors present.

41:07.917 --> 41:09.959
I've been given
a note from the jury.

41:11.750 --> 41:13.083
I'm going to read this note,

41:14.000 --> 41:16.000
then I'm going
to say a few things,

41:16.083 --> 41:19.083
and I don't want any disruptions
while this happens.

41:19.792 --> 41:20.875
Is that clear?

41:29.083 --> 41:30.750
"We tried our best.

41:36.333 --> 41:38.834
-We are deadlocked."
-(GALLERY GASPS, MURMURS)

41:38.917 --> 41:41.125
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Order. Order!
-(GAVEL BANGS)

41:43.083 --> 41:45.750
"We cannot come to a decision."

41:46.959 --> 41:49.458
Sit back down!

41:55.542 --> 41:58.166
I appreciate all the hard work
you've given this court.

41:58.250 --> 42:00.250
Three weeks away
from your families.

42:00.333 --> 42:02.000
Five days of deliberation.

42:04.291 --> 42:06.375
Mr. Foreman,
did you write this note?

42:06.458 --> 42:08.917
-Yes, Your Honor.
-JUDGE WRIGHT: And can I assume

42:09.000 --> 42:11.542
your fellow jurors know
the contents of this note?

42:11.625 --> 42:14.083
-FOREMAN: Yes, Your Honor.
-(GAVEL BANGS)

42:14.166 --> 42:16.166
I am declaring a mistrial.

42:16.250 --> 42:19.000
(GALLERY CLAMORING)

42:19.083 --> 42:22.125
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

42:39.041 --> 42:41.542
(INAUDIBLE)

42:56.667 --> 42:58.417
Let's get out of here. Come on.

42:58.500 --> 43:00.208
We're not answering anything.

43:00.291 --> 43:03.709
(CLAMORING CONTINUES)

43:11.333 --> 43:13.667
BARNES: One at a time, boys.
One at a time.

43:13.750 --> 43:15.959
Yes. We will be
retrying this case.

43:16.041 --> 43:18.125
Absolutely.
Absolutely, absolutely.

43:18.208 --> 43:19.750
You can chisel that in stone.

43:19.834 --> 43:21.417
REPORTER: Mr. Mason,
are you happy?

43:21.500 --> 43:23.125
No-- No, we're not happy.

43:23.208 --> 43:25.041
Emily Dodson
should have been acquitted.

43:25.125 --> 43:26.709
Emily Dodson should
never have been arrested.

43:26.792 --> 43:29.125
BARNES: Well, let me tell you.
Anytime you're in a trial,

43:29.208 --> 43:30.667
there's always
one bullheaded juror

43:30.750 --> 43:32.291
who doesn't know the law,

43:32.375 --> 43:35.709
who thinks it's his or her job
to be contrarian.

43:35.792 --> 43:37.709
Well, it won't happen
at retrial.

43:37.792 --> 43:39.458
The system worked?
In what way?

43:39.542 --> 43:41.375
Because I have
an innocent client here,

43:41.458 --> 43:44.125
undeniably abused
by this system,

43:44.208 --> 43:46.291
by the majority
of your newspapers,

43:46.375 --> 43:47.667
by this court,

43:47.750 --> 43:49.542
by the cops!

43:49.625 --> 43:52.000
Hey, where was he today,
Holcomb?

43:52.083 --> 43:54.375
You keeping that blue line
for him?

43:54.792 --> 43:56.542
Keep walking.

43:56.625 --> 43:58.667
Keep walking, buddy.
Keep walking.

43:58.750 --> 44:00.875
BARNES: I did not lose
the case. (SCOFFS)

44:00.959 --> 44:02.667
It was declared a mistrial,

44:02.750 --> 44:04.667
and it will have no bearing

44:04.750 --> 44:06.834
should I declare
my candidacy for mayor.

44:06.917 --> 44:08.625
Now, let me ask you a question.

44:08.709 --> 44:12.125
What's it like to walk around
with half a fucking brain?

44:12.208 --> 44:15.000
What fucking fish wrap pays you?

44:15.083 --> 44:17.667
All right. I'm fine. I'm fine.

44:17.750 --> 44:20.083
Just wanted to ask
that question.

44:20.166 --> 44:21.417
Emily, you have anything to say

44:21.500 --> 44:23.291
about what happened
at Evergreen Cemetery?

44:23.375 --> 44:25.000
What happened
at Evergreen Cemetery

44:25.083 --> 44:27.583
was a disgrace,
and we wait for the LAPD

44:27.667 --> 44:30.542
to find Charlie's body
and arrest those who stole him.

44:30.625 --> 44:32.125
TROY CHISOM:
And who are you again?

44:32.208 --> 44:34.083
This is Della Street,
my associate.

44:42.792 --> 44:46.917
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

45:05.458 --> 45:07.291
PETE STRICKLAND:
You take the two buses?

45:08.000 --> 45:09.458
I did it just like you said.

45:15.291 --> 45:16.667
That the other half?

45:26.000 --> 45:28.208
This how much you gave
the other two jurors?

45:31.000 --> 45:31.917
What?

45:32.000 --> 45:34.000
JUROR 3:
The other two jurors.

45:34.083 --> 45:37.166
The lady librarian, and the guy
that drives the trolley?

45:37.250 --> 45:39.458
What are you talking about?

45:39.542 --> 45:41.709
We was locked nine to three.

45:41.792 --> 45:44.166
I wanna make sure I'm getting
what they're getting.

45:47.166 --> 45:48.709
I'm the only one getting paid?

45:49.458 --> 45:52.583
(CHUCKLES) Ain't that a kicker.

45:52.667 --> 45:55.333
Guess your housewife
didn't need me after all.

45:57.125 --> 45:59.250
I don't know what
you're talking about, buddy.

46:01.625 --> 46:03.625
I might have guessed
five and ten,

46:03.709 --> 46:05.125
but juror number three?

46:05.208 --> 46:06.750
I mean, who saw that coming?

46:06.834 --> 46:08.625
I'd have given
a hundred-to-one odds,

46:08.709 --> 46:10.458
and still called you a sucker.

46:10.542 --> 46:11.875
Had me fooled.

46:11.959 --> 46:14.291
OLIVER FOGG: You haven't
touched your cake, Mrs. Dodson.

46:14.375 --> 46:16.083
It's awfully tasty.

46:16.166 --> 46:19.166
DELLA: You're a free woman now,
Emily. Go on.

46:21.125 --> 46:22.917
HAZEL PRYSTOCK:
Nothing like a taste of freedom.

46:23.000 --> 46:25.625
♪ ("I FOUND A MILLION DOLLAR
BABY" BY JACK ALBIN'S ORCHESTRA
PLAYING ON RADIO) ♪

46:25.709 --> 46:27.583
DELLA:
Slice for you, Mr. Strickland?

46:28.500 --> 46:30.041
Actually, I'd like a little air.

46:31.208 --> 46:35.083
♪ I found
A million-dollar baby ♪

46:35.166 --> 46:39.208
♪ In a five and ten cent store ♪

46:39.291 --> 46:42.917
♪ Plain little girl
But what a lady ♪

46:43.000 --> 46:47.166
♪ Just the kind
I've been waiting for ♪

46:47.250 --> 46:51.375
♪ Behind the chinaware
She smiled so sweetly ♪

46:51.458 --> 46:55.542
♪ Right then and there
I lost my heart completely ♪

46:55.625 --> 46:59.333
♪ I found
A million-dollar baby ♪

46:59.417 --> 47:03.583
♪ In a five and ten cent store ♪

47:03.667 --> 47:06.041
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

47:09.083 --> 47:11.250
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

47:11.333 --> 47:12.875
(DOG BARKING)

47:15.333 --> 47:16.375
I'm, uh...

47:18.333 --> 47:21.125
I'm gonna go work, uh,
for Hamilton Burger.

47:23.959 --> 47:25.750
-What?
-PETE: DA's Office.

47:26.583 --> 47:28.375
You know, steady work.

47:28.458 --> 47:31.083
Oh, okay. Look,
if you wanna make a point,

47:31.166 --> 47:32.959
just go ahead and make
your fucking point.

47:33.041 --> 47:36.667
I don't think you heard me.
I'm going over to Burger.

47:38.542 --> 47:40.041
MASON: To do what?

47:40.125 --> 47:42.458
Lead investigator.
Get my badge back.

47:44.125 --> 47:47.875
He's, uh, he's going after
the church, following the money.

47:47.959 --> 47:50.542
Oh, you-- you mean the case
I just fucking made?

47:50.625 --> 47:52.291
Listen to you.

47:52.375 --> 47:55.083
-You just don't get it, do you?
-Get what?

47:56.375 --> 47:59.417
Pete, if you need work,
I'll give you work.

47:59.500 --> 48:01.917
Name your salary.

48:02.000 --> 48:04.917
Pete, I need you with me.
You don't even know Burger.

48:05.000 --> 48:06.000
Eh.

48:07.417 --> 48:09.375
You really should be happy, pal.

48:11.333 --> 48:12.458
You won.

48:13.458 --> 48:16.291
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

48:30.667 --> 48:32.667
Mrs. Dodson, how can I help you?

48:39.667 --> 48:40.792
Right this way.

48:43.208 --> 48:45.792
She ran away once as a child.

48:45.875 --> 48:49.125
She came back the next day
with her tail between her legs.

48:49.208 --> 48:52.291
She hid herself in a tree
a couple of avenues away.

48:52.375 --> 48:55.375
She's never been without me
for this long.

48:56.375 --> 48:59.625
There was a sighting
in Albuquerque.

48:59.709 --> 49:03.125
I seriously I doubt the Sister
could have gone that far.

49:03.208 --> 49:06.333
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)
-(BABY COOS)

49:06.417 --> 49:10.625
Well, it's a little past
his bedtime,

49:10.709 --> 49:13.917
but I don't think
he'll hold that against us.

49:15.500 --> 49:17.917
Right. Right, Charlie?

49:18.667 --> 49:20.375
(CHUCKLES)

49:23.250 --> 49:25.875
-(BIRDY COOS)
-I wanna hold him.

49:28.917 --> 49:30.834
(BABY COOING)

49:30.917 --> 49:33.917
Of course.
Of course.

49:35.458 --> 49:37.041
He's been waiting for you.

49:42.875 --> 49:45.291
-(BABY GRUNTS)
-(SHUSHES)

49:47.583 --> 49:50.375
(BIRDY HUMMING)

49:56.250 --> 49:57.959
He's smaller than Charlie.

50:00.375 --> 50:02.041
His arms are shorter.

50:05.125 --> 50:06.625
And his eyes are brown.

50:07.834 --> 50:09.959
(ACOLYTES WHISPERING)

50:11.125 --> 50:12.625
Hi.

50:12.709 --> 50:15.917
Hi. What about this, huh?

50:16.542 --> 50:19.667
Hey. Oh. (GASPS)

50:20.625 --> 50:22.125
(CHUCKLES)

50:26.917 --> 50:28.834
I think he likes the turtle.

50:31.291 --> 50:32.458
(CHUCKLES)

50:35.208 --> 50:36.125
Oh...

50:36.208 --> 50:39.208
-(BLOWS RASPBERRY)
-(EMILY COOS)

50:39.291 --> 50:43.291
(CHUCKLES) Yeah. Yeah.

50:44.458 --> 50:47.667
-(BABY COOING)
-EMILY: Yeah.

50:53.166 --> 50:54.208
(SNIFFLES)

50:56.166 --> 50:59.667
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

51:08.291 --> 51:12.709
♪ ("THE CLOUDS
WILL SOON ROLL BY"
BY BERT AMBROSE PLAYING) ♪

51:17.125 --> 51:21.041
♪ Somewhere
The sun is shining ♪

51:21.125 --> 51:25.250
♪ So, honey, don't you cry... ♪

51:25.333 --> 51:26.667
You ready for this crib?

51:26.750 --> 51:28.583
Watch your step, baby.
You know it...

51:28.667 --> 51:30.792
BURGER: And how did you
come across the evidence

51:30.875 --> 51:33.375
for this financial malfeasance,
Mr. Strickland?

51:33.458 --> 51:35.792
PETE: I was charged with tailing
the church's money man,

51:35.875 --> 51:37.500
-Eric Seidel.
-BURGER: Mm-hmm.

51:37.583 --> 51:40.917
♪ Upon a treetop high... ♪

51:41.000 --> 51:43.291
BIRDY MCKEEGAN:
And I staggered out of that car.

51:43.375 --> 51:46.208
And I heard this crying
in the middle of the road.

51:46.834 --> 51:48.125
And it was this baby boy.

51:48.208 --> 51:50.834
This baby boy was in the middle
of the road crying.

51:50.917 --> 51:54.333
(ALL CHEERING)

51:54.417 --> 51:58.625
BURGER: You became aware of
the Woodland Acres development,

51:58.709 --> 52:02.208
which provided tax shelters
for the elders

52:02.291 --> 52:04.542
of the Radiant Assembly of God?

52:04.625 --> 52:05.583
Yeah.

52:05.667 --> 52:07.083
They're all just
a bunch of crooks

52:07.166 --> 52:08.875
posing as men of the Lord.

52:09.000 --> 52:11.000
And they got all kinds
of ways of doing it.

52:11.083 --> 52:14.500
♪ We'll wander, you and I ♪

52:14.583 --> 52:18.208
♪ Goodbye to stormy weather ♪

52:18.291 --> 52:19.792
♪ The clouds
Will soon roll by... ♪

52:19.875 --> 52:21.750
BIRDY: And I delivered
this baby boy

52:21.834 --> 52:23.834
into this mother's arms.
Didn't I do that, Sister Dodson?

52:23.917 --> 52:26.083
EMILY: Yes, you did,
Mother McKeegan, and I held him.

52:26.166 --> 52:30.333
And I knew that he was my son
resurrected from death.

52:30.417 --> 52:32.542
Resurrected from death.

52:32.625 --> 52:35.458
-Delivered by heaven, right?
-(SCATTERED APPLAUSE)

52:35.542 --> 52:36.625
-Right?
-MAN: Yeah!

52:36.709 --> 52:38.750
Because God wants us
to see these miracles.

52:38.834 --> 52:40.333
God wants us
to see these miracles.

52:40.417 --> 52:43.250
Who here has had a miracle, huh?
Raise those hands.

52:43.333 --> 52:44.500
I'm talking to you.

52:44.583 --> 52:47.792
Oh, boy. We have some
believers in this audience.

52:52.959 --> 52:55.667
DELLA: I'll answer the phones,
keep the office in shape,

52:55.750 --> 52:56.917
maintain the files,

52:57.000 --> 53:00.375
and I'll take notes for you
when you're with clients.

53:00.458 --> 53:03.125
I'll do all of that because
we have no money at the moment.

53:03.208 --> 53:05.792
But the minute we do,
we're hiring a girl.

53:07.458 --> 53:10.291
Leaving you
with what to do?

53:10.375 --> 53:13.250
Continuing with all
the other things I'll be doing.

53:13.333 --> 53:16.250
Executing wills,
handling real estate closures,

53:16.333 --> 53:18.875
the bread and butter
of a small firm.

53:18.959 --> 53:21.291
-I see.
-DELLA: And when we go
to trial again,

53:21.375 --> 53:22.625
I'll be writing up
motions for you,

53:22.709 --> 53:25.291
preparing witnesses,
advising you on jury selection.

53:25.375 --> 53:27.125
That sounds like
the work of a lawyer.

53:27.208 --> 53:28.917
DELLA: Which I will be
in two years,

53:29.000 --> 53:32.250
because you'll be paying for my
night classes at City College.

53:33.875 --> 53:36.959
And when I pass the bar,
Mason and Associates

53:37.041 --> 53:38.500
will be Mason and Street.

53:42.291 --> 53:44.709
You two know there's a client
waiting in the other room?

53:44.792 --> 53:46.709
-DELLA: We're almost done.
-Yeah. We're negotiating.

53:46.792 --> 53:48.750
Getting your ass
handed to you, more like it.

53:48.834 --> 53:51.000
DELLA: You'll pay me
what E.B. was paying me,

53:51.083 --> 53:52.250
plus 20 percent.

53:52.333 --> 53:57.125
And any quarterly profits, huh,
will be split sixty-forty.

53:57.208 --> 53:59.667
-Ninety-ten.
-Mmm, sixty-forty.

53:59.750 --> 54:01.583
I'd like to be paid in cash
while you two

54:01.667 --> 54:03.500
-build the business.
-We have a client waiting.

54:03.583 --> 54:06.333
Let's, uh...
let's haggle about this later.

54:07.000 --> 54:08.291
So who is the client?

54:08.375 --> 54:10.959
A woman who claims to be
a Mrs. Eva Griffin.

54:11.041 --> 54:13.417
-"Claims"?
-Yeah, she looks phony to me.

54:13.500 --> 54:15.625
I looked up all the Griffins
in the city directory.

54:15.709 --> 54:19.000
There's a lot of Griffins,
but there is no Eva Griffin.

54:19.083 --> 54:22.000
-What do I need you for?
-Thinking the same thing.

54:22.083 --> 54:24.041
You're gonna make
a great lady lawyer.

54:24.125 --> 54:27.458
I'm gonna make
a great lawyer, no modifier.

54:27.542 --> 54:29.041
(QUIETLY) Yeah, no modifier.

54:31.709 --> 54:33.625
Found that address
you was looking for.

54:33.709 --> 54:34.709
Oh.

54:37.458 --> 54:39.208
DRAKE:
Expenses on the back side.

54:40.250 --> 54:41.583
You got receipts?

54:41.667 --> 54:43.917
Or you can just
take my word for it.

54:44.834 --> 54:46.750
DELLA: Right this way,
Mrs. Griffin.

54:49.834 --> 54:52.125
You're Mr. Mason, the attorney?

54:52.208 --> 54:54.000
MASON: I am.
You've met Della.

54:54.083 --> 54:55.458
This is my other associate,
Paul Drake.

54:55.542 --> 54:57.542
One of the best detectives
in the city.

54:57.625 --> 54:58.625
Pleased.

55:00.583 --> 55:03.125
So, what brings you in today,
Mrs. Griffin?

55:08.250 --> 55:09.375
I'm in trouble.

55:12.041 --> 55:13.959
And she can pay the retainer.

55:15.417 --> 55:17.125
You've come to the right place.

55:18.375 --> 55:21.875
AL HOWARD: Put a roof over it.
More gaming space.

55:23.208 --> 55:27.083
A new indoor fountain.
Maybe get some, uh--

55:28.250 --> 55:30.542
What do you call them?
Uh... (GROANS)

55:31.417 --> 55:33.291
-Those big goldfish?
-Koi.

55:33.917 --> 55:35.041
HOWARD: Yeah?

55:35.625 --> 55:36.959
No, that ain't it.

55:37.041 --> 55:39.375
I wish I had your smarts,
Mr. Howard.

55:39.458 --> 55:41.166
You got a real knack
for business.

55:41.250 --> 55:42.542
(HOWARD CHUCKLES)

55:42.625 --> 55:46.458
You boys want the envelope or,
uh, double it in house credit?

55:46.542 --> 55:47.792
How about it, Gene?

55:48.625 --> 55:49.750
The envelope.

55:50.625 --> 55:52.583
You always were the smart one.

55:52.667 --> 55:54.959
-Regards to Woo Sing.
-Sure.

55:55.959 --> 55:57.333
Double in credit, huh?

55:57.417 --> 56:00.041
Could've done something
with that. Who knows?

56:00.125 --> 56:01.583
Listen, Joe...

56:02.875 --> 56:05.041
if anything ever happens to me,

56:05.125 --> 56:07.291
make sure
Maddy gets my share, okay?

56:07.375 --> 56:08.417
Of course.

56:08.500 --> 56:10.917
And if anything
were to happen to you, uh,

56:11.000 --> 56:13.041
I'll do likewise.

56:13.125 --> 56:16.792
Look, I want you know, uh,
Elaine and the kids...

56:18.792 --> 56:20.959
they're gonna be okay.

56:21.041 --> 56:24.458
-♪ (INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(GRUNTING)

56:28.166 --> 56:29.417
What the fuck?

56:29.500 --> 56:31.208
Get the fuck...

56:31.291 --> 56:33.709
(GRUNTING)

56:38.208 --> 56:39.750
(GARDENER SHOUTS MANDARIN)

56:39.834 --> 56:41.834
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

56:42.333 --> 56:43.500
(SCREAMS)

56:49.959 --> 56:51.333
(SHOUTING IN MANDARIN)

56:56.625 --> 56:59.291
(WATER SPLASHING)

57:00.000 --> 57:02.375
(SHOUTING IN MANDARIN)

57:03.709 --> 57:05.375
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

57:08.083 --> 57:10.208
(SPLASHING QUIETS)

57:25.041 --> 57:27.709
(MEN BREATHING HEAVILY)

57:40.375 --> 57:41.542
Sorry, Joe.

57:48.500 --> 57:50.875
WAITRESS: Hope you don't mind
me getting this settled.

57:50.959 --> 57:52.291
My shift's about over.

57:52.375 --> 57:54.917
Gotta go cook for them
what's home now.

57:55.333 --> 57:57.125
Keep the change.

57:57.208 --> 57:59.709
-WAITRESS: Ah, appreciate you.
-Yeah.

58:03.750 --> 58:05.583
WAITRESS: Hey, sweetie.

58:05.667 --> 58:08.625
♪ (JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING
ON RADIO) ♪

58:20.250 --> 58:21.959
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

58:24.417 --> 58:26.667
Pretty long way from the choir.

58:26.750 --> 58:28.458
SISTER ALICE MCKEEGAN:
It's not so far.

58:29.625 --> 58:31.583
There's an old mission
up the road.

58:31.667 --> 58:33.667
I go there sometimes
and I pray.

58:34.458 --> 58:36.083
You get any answers?

58:38.792 --> 58:39.959
Not lately.

58:49.250 --> 58:51.458
MASON: They're running
a circuit down south.

58:52.125 --> 58:55.125
Temecula, Encinitas, Escondido.

58:55.208 --> 58:57.458
Fairly popular
from what I hear.

58:59.875 --> 59:03.583
You didn't come all this way
to show me this, did you?

59:05.125 --> 59:06.834
I know how Charlie died.

59:08.000 --> 59:10.417
I know that Ennis put a crew
together and took him.

59:10.500 --> 59:12.709
I know that Gannon found out
about Baggerly.

59:12.792 --> 59:15.041
I know that Seidel had
a hundred-thousand-dollar hole

59:15.125 --> 59:16.542
that he was trying to fill.

59:17.583 --> 59:21.041
I knew all those things,
but I couldn't prove it.

59:21.125 --> 59:23.417
The trial's over, Mr. Mason.
You won.

59:23.500 --> 59:27.333
-There's one thing I wanna know.
-Whether or not I'm a fraud?

59:29.583 --> 59:32.166
Someone took that boy's body
out of the ground.

59:33.417 --> 59:36.417
That's quite a trick to pull
with everybody watching.

59:36.500 --> 59:37.667
Even for God.

59:39.333 --> 59:42.750
You really do wanna believe
in Him, don't you?

59:42.834 --> 59:47.667
No matter how hard you try,
you still hope that He's there.

59:51.375 --> 59:55.125
A baby was killed
to prop up your church.

59:55.208 --> 59:58.875
So you're telling me
that you can look at this

59:59.792 --> 1:00:01.250
and you can still believe?

1:00:02.500 --> 1:00:04.375
You wanna know things,
Mr. Mason.

1:00:04.458 --> 1:00:08.375
You wanna find things out
and prove things.

1:00:09.583 --> 1:00:11.709
What comfort
has that ever given you?

1:00:11.792 --> 1:00:14.375
-(CHUCKLES)
-ALICE: What peace?

1:00:19.041 --> 1:00:21.208
When I saw you in there,
out of the blue,

1:00:21.291 --> 1:00:23.208
I thought maybe...

1:00:24.083 --> 1:00:26.458
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

1:00:26.542 --> 1:00:28.875
...maybe you were tired
of being alone.

1:00:30.583 --> 1:00:31.875
Maybe I am.

1:00:35.583 --> 1:00:36.792
I am too.

1:00:44.959 --> 1:00:47.208
But we will be, won't we?

1:00:48.125 --> 1:00:49.375
Alone?

1:00:55.625 --> 1:00:57.041
Why is that?

1:01:11.333 --> 1:01:12.625
Goodbye, Perry.

1:01:20.208 --> 1:01:21.250
Wait.

1:01:24.500 --> 1:01:27.125
Did you really think
you could bring Charlie back?

1:01:29.291 --> 1:01:30.917
I did, didn't I?

1:01:35.125 --> 1:01:37.959
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

1:02:16.834 --> 1:02:20.500
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

1:04:15.333 --> 1:04:17.125
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
